top_comments: I admit… I may have had a little too much fun filming this video ha ha! I certainly hope you enjoyed it! Thanks for watching! ￼

Former HF employee. In practical terms, about the only thing their safes are good for is meeting minimum gun storage standards for the absolute bottom dollar. They are stout enough to slow down a casual thief, but anyone with some basic knowledge and the right tools are going to be in that box and gone in under three minutes. The little fire safe is actually good. Had a customer lose damn near everything in a house fire. The contents of the dinky little safe he had smelled like smoke, but were otherwise undamaged.
